						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the central shrine in the Vīraṭṭāṉēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Rājēndrachōḻa I Year 2 = 1014 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This records the gift of 96 sheep, by Maṭṭai Suṟṟiyaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Rājarājavānakōn a manṟāḍi, of Vaḍaiyil-nāḍu, a division of Palūr-kūṟṟam, for burning a perpetual lamp to the god Tiruvīraṭṭānamuḍaiyār at Tirukkovalur, in Kuṟukṭkai-kūṟṟam a district of Jananātha-vaḷanāḍu <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Milāḍu, a sub-division of Jayanggoṇḍa-chōḻa-maṇḍalam.</p>						

						</summary>
